msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:14
msgid "Adds a compressor audio effect to an audio bus."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:16
msgid ""
"Reduces sounds that exceed a certain threshold level, smooths out the "
"dynamics and increases the overall volume."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:19
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:21
msgid ""
"Dynamic range compressor reduces the level of the sound when the "
"amplitude goes over a certain threshold in Decibels. One of the main uses"
" of a compressor is to increase the dynamic range by clipping as little "
"as possible (when sound goes over 0dB)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:23
msgid "Compressor has many uses in the mix:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:25
msgid ""
"In the Master bus to compress the whole output (although an "
":ref:`AudioEffectLimiter <class_AudioEffectLimiter>` is probably better)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:27
msgid "In voice channels to ensure they sound as balanced as possible."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:29
msgid ""
"Sidechained. This can reduce the sound level sidechained with another "
"audio bus for threshold detection. This technique is common in video game"
" mixing to the level of music and SFX while voices are being heard."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_audioeffectcompressor.rst:31
msgid ""
"Accentuates transients by using a wider attack, making effects sound more"
" punchy."
msgstr ""

